JOHN PIERPONT, Gen. S. F. CARY, Dr. LYMAN BEECHER and others.

abstract: General DIX's friends should make haste to sympathise with him. I state from undoubted authority, that Gen CASS has been handsomely offered the French Mission. abstract: It will be recollected that Commodore NEWTON's death was published in most of the newspapers, which was erroneous, as he is still alive. abstract: Accounts from Montevideo, July 25, represent the state of political affairs there on the brink of another revolution. There were two parties actively preparing to submit their rival claims to an arbitrament of arms--the "Reds" and the "Whites." The fever is decreasing rapidly, and the Society advise us that they have all the funds necessary for the relief of the sick, thanks to a generous, charitable people.

abstract: Five yachts started yesterday morning on a race to Marcus Hook and back, for a purse of $500. abstract: The New York City Guards have shown themselves worthy of noble guests. The "Crack Companies " of the two great cities enjoyed themselves last night. It was truly a great time.

abstract: Louisiana, in its physical character, in its history, and in the native stock of its population, is very different from any other part of our country. There is no State which shows so many marks of having been long lived in by a civilized people--in which there is so much that is antique and respectable with age, and yet none in which the flow of young, enterprising, active life is greater.

abstract: The Times has been excluded from Spain by a royal decree published in the official Gazette. Our contemporary is justified in boasting of this exclusion as a tribute paid to his influence in the cause of truth.
